item.description:
       After you have save your feature model, FeatureIDE will create directories for each feature. In this directories you can create Jak-Files.


Start to create a new Jak-file in the directory Hello: Right-Click on the Directory and use the context-item New->Jak File. Choose the container "hello" and use "Main" for the Class name.


Open the file und write the following code:


public void print(){

  System.out.print("Hello");

}

public static void main(String[args]) {

  new Main.print();

}

       Now edit the remaining jak-Files. Every feature will refine the method print() in the Main class.

 Now insert the following code in your world feature: 


	public void print() {

		Super().print();

		System.out.print(" world!");

	}


	In the other files you can insert the same code and just change the print method.

For example:

System.out.print(" wonderful"); in the "wonderful" feature.
System.out.print(" beautiful");
 in the "beautiful" feature.
